name: Danny Fong
reviewContext/Recommended dishes: Green Peppers with Slice Pork, Golden Broth Sour and Spicy Fish
text:
Apparently this is a home grown brand restaurant (if i am wrong. someone please correct me). As the restaurant name its Hunan cuisine; tbh i can‚Äôt tell the difference from Yunnan, Hunan or Shanghai food but i can tell what is good and whats not.

First time here, the food is delicious, in my opinion the portions are a little small i guess the strategy is order more and try everything. we were a party of 8 and we managed to try a few more things.

What is really like is, food here is not too salty. my 2 fav is the Sauerkraut Fish and Vermicelli (we ordered the 2nd one before the first one is done). because of this we ended up ordering too much rice - one pot of it feed 5 ppl. they also serve little bag of crackers and small cups of ice cream (like HDL).

The service team is very attentive and fast and oh the dishes are served faster than McDonalds on busy day üòÑ. what i was told is this place is typically busy during meal times and they DON‚ÄôT take reservations on weekends.

text:
I had the pleasure of dining at Xiang Xiang, food is very delicious especially the stir fried angus beef and I have to say, Amy, our waitress, made the entire experience exceptional! From the moment we were seated, she greeted us with a warm smile and a friendly demeanor that instantly put us at ease.
Amy was attentive throughout the meal, ensuring our glasses were always full and that we had everything we needed. She knew the menu inside and out, giving excellent recommendations for both food and drinks, and even accommodated a couple of special requests without hesitation. Her professionalism and efficiency were top-notch, but what really stood out was her genuine kindness and upbeat attitude.

name: Jaryl Teo
text: I recently dined at Xiang Xiang and was blown away by their cauliflower dish and fried vermicelli. The cauliflower was perfectly cooked, with just the right balance of tenderness and crunch, infused with a savory sauce that had a great depth of flavor. It was a delightful surprise for a vegetable dish! The fried vermicelli was equally impressive‚Äîlight, not greasy, and full of flavor with a satisfying mix of textures. Both dishes showcased the chef's attention to detail and authentic flavors. I will definitely be coming back for more!
